> Getting Started with Shell Scripting


Basic Steps:


Step1: Get what manual commmands are to be Scripted

Step2: Write Shell script -
	- open text file with extension .sh
	- write first line as shebang or interpreter (#!/bin/bash or #!/bin/zsh)
	- type or paste manual commands to be executed in sequence
  
Step3: Executing shell script
	- provide execution permission by 
  >> chmod +x xyz.sh
	- when in same directory run with 
  >> ./xyz.sh         
    or else by complete path 
  >> /home/user/xyz.sh
